==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bosky
<hw>Bosk"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Bushy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Woody or bushy; covered with
boscage or thickets.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Caused by boscage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Darkened over by long <qex>bosky</qex> shadows.</q> <rj><qau>H.
James.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bo's'n</ent>⟦br⟧
